menu "breadboard: bb_http_client"

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_KEEPALIVE
    bool "Enable TCP/TLS keep-alive on reusable sessions"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_http_client_session_open sets keep_alive_enable=true
        on the underlying esp_http_client so the TCP/TLS connection is reused
        across bb_http_client_session_post calls (lower latency per publish).
        Disable to open+close a fresh connection on every session_post call
        (higher latency, no idle-socket wedge risk).  The default (y) preserves
        the behaviour prior to B1-284.

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS
    int "Default request timeout (ms)"
    default 10000
    range 1000 120000
    help
        Default per-request timeout for bb_http_client_get when cfg.timeout_ms
        is 0.

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_MAX_ATTEMPTS
    int "Default retry attempts"
    default 3
    range 1 10
    help
        Default number of transport attempts before giving up.

config BB_HTTP_CLIENT_TASK_STACK_SIZE
    int "Minimum task stack size for callers of bb_http_client_get* (bytes)"
    default 8192
    range 4096 16384
    help
        Any FreeRTOS task that calls bb_http_client_get or
        bb_http_client_get_stream must allocate at least this much stack to
        cover the mbedTLS handshake + cert-bundle parse path. 8 KiB is the
        empirically-validated floor on ESP32-S3; 4 KiB overflows into adjacent
        heap. Use the BB_HTTP_CLIENT_TASK_STACK macro from bb_http_client.h
        when calling xTaskCreate so the budget stays consistent across
        consumers.

        Note: the TLS handshake also requires a contiguous internal heap block
        of roughly CONFIG_MBEDTLS_SSL_IN_CONTENT_LEN bytes at handshake time.
        On no-PSRAM pull-strategy boards, bb_ota_pull's pre-flight guard
        (CONFIG_BB_OTA_PULL_MIN_HEAP_BLOCK_BYTES) enforces this at runtime.

endmenu
